      },
      "media": {
        "id": "fs-idp75347888",
        "alt": "Two diagrams are shown. Diagram a contains two molecules whose p orbitals, which are depicted as two balloon-shaped structures that meet together to form a peanut shape, are laid end over end, creating an area of overlap. In diagram b, the same two molecules are shown, but this time, they are laid out in a way so as to form a near-ninety degree angle. In this diagram, the ends of two of these peanut-shaped orbitals do not overlap nearly as much.",
        "src": "../../media/CNX_Chem_08_01_overlap.jpg",
        "mimeType": "image/jpeg"
      }
    },
